<!--
  FormXml patch — hosts InsightSummaryCard on Matter form
  =======================================================

  Task 042 deliverable. Adds:
    1. A new <library> registration for `sprk_/scripts/matter_insight_card_mount.js`
       on the Matter main form's events collection.
    2. A new <Handler> binding wiring the library's `Spaarke.MatterInsightCard.onLoad`
       function to the form's OnLoad event (in addition to existing handlers).
    3. A new <control> of class "WebResource" inside the existing Matter Health
       card section, pointing at the HTML host web resource that wraps the
       `<div id="spaarke-matter-insight-card-host"></div>` mount target.

  Companion artefacts shipped together in Task 043 (solution package):
    - Web resource: sprk_/scripts/matter_insight_card_mount.js
       (compiled output of insightCardMount.ts)
    - Web resource: sprk_/html/matter_insight_card_host.html
       (static HTML containing the mount target div + bundle <script> tag)
    - Web resource: sprk_/scripts/matter_insight_onload.js
       (Task 040/041 deliverable; already registered separately per FR-18)
    - Web resource: sprk_/scripts/spaarke_ai_widgets_bundle.js
       (Task 043 deliverable — IIFE bundle of @spaarke/ai-widgets + React;
        exposes `window.SpaarkeAiWidgets.mountInsightSummaryCard`)

  This file is a PATCH (not a full FormXml replacement). The Task 043 solution
  packaging step merges these fragments into the exported Matter form XML.

  Form / control / section identifiers
  -------------------------------------
  Tab name:       "tab_matter_health"
  Section name:   "section_matter_health_card"
  Control name:   "WebResource_matter_insight_card"   (NEW per this patch)
  Library name:   "sprk_/scripts/matter_insight_card_mount.js"   (NEW per this patch)

  Both tab and section names mirror the existing "Matter Health card" surface
  from matter-performance-KPI-r1 (verified via Task 002 R5 sparkle-wiring
  baseline grep — the section exists and is the canonical "Matter Health"
  surface on the Matter form). Final solution packaging (Task 043) MUST verify
  the tab/section identifiers against the actual exported FormXml — names are
  often suffixed (e.g., `tab_5`, `section_3`) by the platform.

  Coexistence rules
  -----------------
  - The existing `Spaarke.MatterInsight.onLoad` (Task 040/041, pre-warm) and
    `Spaarke.MatterKpi.onLoad` (matter-performance-KPI-r1) handlers are
    UNCHANGED. Both remain registered alongside the new
    `Spaarke.MatterInsightCard.onLoad`.
  - Handler order: `Spaarke.MatterInsight.onLoad` (pre-warm) SHOULD fire before
    `Spaarke.MatterInsightCard.onLoad` (render) so the pre-warm POST is
    in-flight by the time the card mounts. The platform fires OnLoad handlers
    in registered order; Task 043 verifies via the exported FormXml.
-->

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 1. Library registration (Matter form events.libraries)       -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->
<libraries-patch>
  <!--
    Append this <library> entry to <events><libraries> in the Matter main form's
    customizations.xml. The library `sprk_/scripts/matter_insight_card_mount.js`
    is added as a NEW entry; existing entries (matter_insight_onload.js,
    matter_kpi_onload.js, etc.) are preserved.
  -->
  <library name="sprk_/scripts/matter_insight_card_mount.js" libraryUniqueId="{REPLACE-WITH-NEW-GUID}" />
</libraries-patch>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 2. OnLoad handler binding (Matter form events.event[OnLoad]) -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->
<handlers-patch>
  <!--
    Append this <Handler> entry to the <event name="OnLoad"> <Handlers> collection.
    Preserves existing handlers (Spaarke.MatterInsight.onLoad, Spaarke.MatterKpi.onLoad).
  -->
  <Handler
    functionName="Spaarke.MatterInsightCard.onLoad"
    libraryName="sprk_/scripts/matter_insight_card_mount.js"
    handlerUniqueId="{REPLACE-WITH-NEW-GUID}"
    enabled="true"
    parameters=""
    passExecutionContext="true" />
</handlers-patch>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 3. WebResource control on Matter Health card section         -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->
<section-control-patch
  targetTab="tab_matter_health"
  targetSection="section_matter_health_card">
  <!--
    Append this <row><cell><control/></cell></row> to the Matter Health card
    section's <rows> collection. The control hosts a Power Apps WebResource
    that renders the static HTML containing the mount target div.

    width / height are starter values — Task 043 + Task 044 UX verification may
    tune them. Width "fillRow" stretches the control to the section column
    width (recommended for the card render surface).
  -->
  <row>
    <cell id="{REPLACE-WITH-NEW-GUID}" showLabel="false" rowSpan="6" colSpan="2" auto="false">
      <labels>
        <label description="Matter Health Insight" languagecode="1033" />
      </labels>
      <control
        id="WebResource_matter_insight_card"
        classid="{9FDF5F91-88B1-47F4-AD53-C11EFC01A01D}"
        indicationOfSubgrid="false">
        <parameters>
          <Url>$webresource:sprk_/html/matter_insight_card_host.html</Url>
          <PassParameters>false</PassParameters>
          <Security>false</Security>
          <Scrolling>auto</Scrolling>
          <Border>false</Border>
        </parameters>
      </control>
    </cell>
  </row>
</section-control-patch>

<!--
  ============================================================
  4. Companion HTML host web resource (separate file)
  ============================================================

  The web resource at `sprk_/html/matter_insight_card_host.html` MUST contain:

      <!DOCTYPE html>
      <html lang="en">
        <head>
          <meta charset="utf-8" />
          <title>Matter Health Insight</title>
          <style>
            html, body { margin: 0; padding: 0; height: 100%; background: transparent; }
            #spaarke-matter-insight-card-host {
              width: 100%;
              min-height: 200px;
              padding: 8px;
              box-sizing: border-box;
            }
          </style>
        </head>
        <body>
          <div id="spaarke-matter-insight-card-host"></div>
          <!-- React + ReactDOM + @spaarke/ai-widgets IIFE bundle (Task 043) -->
          <script src="../scripts/spaarke_ai_widgets_bundle.js"></script>
        </body>
      </html>

  The bundle script attaches `window.SpaarkeAiWidgets.mountInsightSummaryCard`,
  which the parent form's `insightCardMount.js` invokes (the form-side handler
  reaches into the iframe via the WebResource control's DOM bridge — Task 043
  finalises the bridge mechanism if direct `getElementById` from the parent
  scope is unavailable).

  Cross-frame note
  ----------------
  Power Apps "WebResource" controls render inside an iframe. The mount glue
  in `insightCardMount.ts` uses `document.getElementById(...)` which runs in
  the PARENT (form) document; if the host div lives inside the iframe, the
  resolution will fail and the mount will fall through to the warning log
  ("host element not found"). Task 043 chooses one of two paths:
    (a) Move the mount glue itself INTO the html web resource (so it runs in
        the iframe scope) — simplest, isolates the React render entirely;
    (b) Expose a `window.parent.Spaarke.MatterInsightCard._registerHost(...)`
        bridge from the iframe to the parent — more complex, allows the parent
        OnLoad handler to drive the lifecycle.

  Task 042 ships the contract; Task 043 chooses (a) or (b) and updates this
  patch + the html web resource accordingly.

  ============================================================
  5. Solution packaging (Task 043 scope)
  ============================================================

  Task 043 packages this patch + the .js compiled output + the html web
  resource + the bundle web resource into a single managed solution and
  imports to dev/UAT/prod via `pac solution import` per the canonical
  Spaarke dataverse-deploy pattern.
-->
